# AI Agents & MCP

Follow `docs/AI_AGENTS.md`, `docs/MCP.md`, `docs/WORKFLOWS.md`.

## Agents

- Master Orchestrator plans/routes; domain agents own tools — no god prompt.
- Config-driven `AgentDefinition`: prompts versioned, tool allowlists, budgets, flags.
- Structured plan JSON schema-validated before execution.
- Risk policy: low auto; medium+ confirmation; critical via workflow approval.
- Durable approvals belong in Workflow Engine — not LLM memory.

## MCP

- Vendor-agnostic tool names (`applyLeave`, not `kekaApplyLeave`).
- Credentials injected by gateway from vault — never from the model.
- Log redacted tool calls with latency/status; timeouts + circuit breakers required.

## Never

Invent tools · silent mutating calls · business logic only inside a vendor adapter with no workflow visibility.
